When you run `pyblosxom-cmd --config=somedir/config.py` while you happen to be
in a directory which contains a config.py, pyblosxom-cmd will load and use it.
pyblosxom-cmd should never do this, and read only from where you tell it to.

Demo:
$ ls -alh /srv/http/dieterblog/config.py # perfectly fine config.py
-rw-r--r-- 1 http http 6.8K Oct 31 17:11 /srv/http/dieterblog/config.py
$ mkdir tmp && cd tmp
$ touch config.py
$ pyblosxom-cmd renderurl --config=/srv/http/dieterblog/config.py /
pyblosxom-cmd version 1.5rc2 20100803
Adding /srv/http/dieterblog/ to sys.path....
Trying to import the config module....
ERROR: Cannot find your config.py file.  Please execute pyblosxom-cmd in
the directory with the config.py file in it or use the --config flag.
See "pyblosxom-cmd --help" for more details.
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/usr/bin/pyblosxom-cmd", line 5, in <module>
    pkg_resources.run_script('pyblosxom==1.5rc2', 'pyblosxom-cmd')
  File "/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/pkg_resources.py", line 467, in run_script
    self.require(requires)[0].run_script(script_name, ns)
  File "/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/pkg_resources.py", line 1200, in run_script
    execfile(script_filename, namespace, namespace)
